issue.title: Enable/Install WSL within a Docker Windows container
issue.body:
Hi everyone,

I am wanting to enable and install the Windows Subsystem for Linux (WSL) feature from within a Docker windowsservrecore container.
However, due to the fact that Docker containers are more like full-environment-processes than VMs,
and because WSL feature installation requires a 'system reboot'; this has proven troublesome.

I have seen solutions that other people have figured out for installing features that normally 'require reboot' in a Docker windows container.
- e.g. Active Directory support: [](https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/containerstuff/2017/01/30/create-a-container-with-active-directory-support/)
- e.g. Server Media Foundation: [](https://forums.docker.com/t/installing-server-media-foundation-in-a-docker-container/23587)

So I was wondering if anyone had any thoughts or has managed something similar for getting WSL to install in a Docker windows container?

Thanks in advance.

issue.title: BC controller:  when save fails, better error page to user
issue.body:
When the app fails, it gives the generic rails error page, which isn't a good user experience.  Moreover, developer needs to troll through rails logs to find out what error was thrown and any messages.

It would be better if we gave a better error page to the user, complete with error information and what the end_user should DO (like, send an email to some list, or call Donald Trump or something)

comment.body: It is pretty conventional to render the "new" template again (i.e. where they were coming from) with the object-that-has-errors.  That way it has their old values and they get another shot at modifying them (ideally prompted by a friendly error message).
